<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-01T20:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-01T20:49:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1124.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-01T21:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1915—9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your February 27, 2 p.m. Have arranged with Admiral Caperton that <hi rend="italic">Wheeling</hi> be at Cape Haitien on March 3 to bring
                            Consul Livingston Port au Prince. No means communication with
                            Livingston. Please advise him at once to be ready.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>